post_text:
Grapeland ISD Sandiette Athletics has received a donation from a former Sandiette who would like to remain anonymous in the name of former Sandiette Basketball Coach Mr. Chuck Bailey, former teacher and coach of the 1989‚Äô Girls State Champion basketball team from Grapeland. He passed away in his home surrounded by family on Sunday, August 23rd in Weatherford TX. Coach Bailey was one of those coaches who pushed his players to be the best version of themselves on and off the court. It was that kind of determination that not only led to championships but also to how he tackled his own obstacles. Coach Bailey will be forever remembered for the integrity he sought to instill and the passion he had for the game. Thank you, Coach.
-Former Sandiette Basketball Player

post_text:
Grapeland Football vs. Shelbyville
Fri. 7:30 PM; Sandie Stadium
COVID PROTOCOLS must be followed:
Tickets must be purchased in advance at GISD Admin Office Starting Friday at 8:30 AM; Spectators will be screened and may be refused entry; All fans will be asked to sit in the stands with their family and no standing will be allowed on the fence; All spectators age 10 and up will be expected to wear face coverings and practice social distancing; GISD will restrict stadium seating to 50% capacity; all fans will be asked to follow traffic patterns in entering and exiting the field to help mitigate COVID spread; Concessions will be sold but fans will be asked to social distance in the concession lines. After the game, the team wil go directly into the locker room and no fans will be allowed onto the field. Administrators will be on duty to monitor and enforce these protocols. All parents are ask to keep children under their watchful eye and not allow them to roam the stadium. Thank you in advance for your cooperation.

shared_text:
Jenifer Allen Canter
August 1 at 8:02 AM ¬∑

It is just what teachers do.

Every year lately we have been faced with difficult events. Harvey, Imelda, deaths, change. Are we perfect? No. Are we going to get everything right automatically? Probably not. Are we going to love the kids whole heartedly and do everything we can to show up and be their normal and assure them we are ALL getting through this TOGETHER? ABSOLUTELY!

Are we creating things that then will get tossed out? Sure. Are we wanting to know what this will look like? Of course. Are we on the inside freaking out because we need to seem we have it pulled together? Possibly.

BUT.....this is why I love education and my school district.

We are the calm in the chaos, the steady in the ever-changing, the certain in so much uncertainty. We will support our kids and our parents no matter what that looks like.

post_text: Hello Everyone. Just reminding you that Band Camp is happening these next couple of weeks. There has been some time changes to accommodate our busiest students schedules. We start at 7 am every morning so students can get used to the new start time for band in the mornings this upcoming school year. The band will meet at 7 am and except for special circumstances, students who do not arrive on time will receive extra assignments in Band. We hope everyone is well and ask that you stay safe while we continue to build our program up during this difficult time. Thank you!

Attention Parents: Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Tomorrow, April 9, 2020 at the Grapeland Elementary School the Grapeland Police Department officers will be passing out Easter Baggies! Each bag is filled with stuffed eggs and other assorted goodies.

Officer's will be at curbside with the school staff from 10:00AM - 1:00PM while children and parents collect homework packets for the week.

Hidden among the Easter baggies are 30+ randomly placed prize eggs. If you receive a prize egg please follow the directions inside!

Please note this will be for Grapeland ISD students during essential school packet/meal pickup times to refrain from non-essential travel.

As always, please stay safe!

post_text:
Clean your hands often
Wash your hands often with soap and water for at least 20 seconds especially after you have been in a public place, or after blowing your nose, coughing, or sneezing.
If soap and water are not readily available, use a hand sanitizer that contains at least 60% alcohol. Cover all surfaces of your hands and rub them together until they feel dry.
Avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth with unwashed hands.
"Because Emergencies Do Happen."

UIL Academic State Events Postponed Due to COVID-19

AUSTIN ‚Äî Amid growing concerns over COVID-19 (coronavirus), the UIL CX Debate State Tournament and the UIL State Robotics FIRST Tech Challenge will be postponed until further notice. Participating schools will be notified directly by UIL with updates as they become available.

‚ÄúThe health and safety of our students and schools is our number one priority,‚Äù said UIL Executive Director Dr. Charles Breithaupt, ‚ÄúIt is crucial we take every possible precaution to keep participants safe.‚Äù

As this is a fluid situation, the UIL will continue to follow the direction of local officials to monitor this situation and will make additional announcements as needed. Please continue to check the UIL website and social media accounts for further updates.
